BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finding the Issues in Our Stories and the Stories in Our Issues: A
  Member Exclusive Webinar
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T180000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T180000
UID:9aa0984169a0a2500ad596efcee54030@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:The current fraught socio-political climate is motivating writ
 ers to engage with social issues on the page. The personal is political\, 
 and the political is personal. In truth\, the writer has long played a rol
 e as a witness\, conscience\, and predictor of social change. How do we wr
 ite compellingly yet responsibly about social issues? By grappling with th
 e social issues at the core of our stories and by harnessing the narrative
  elements of stories embedded in the social issues we care about.\nWe are 
 thrilled to host\nKavita Das\n\, author of\nCraft and Conscience: How to W
 rite About Social\nIssues\n\, for a member-exclusive webinar about the rel
 ationship between the writer\, reader\, and subject\, and how writers can 
 think about applying the notions of context and narrative to their work. P
 articipants will have the opportunity to engage in writing exercises that 
 allow them to apply lessons on how they might balance doing justice to the
  issues they care about while telling a good story.\nThis is a member-excl
 usive event. If you are a member\, please visit the\nmember benefits\npage
  to access the registration link. Not a PEN America member?\nJoin today!\n
 Kavita Das\nis currently a Masters in Fine Arts candidate in creative nonf
 iction and screenwriting at Antioch University where she is the Eloise Kle
 in Healy Scholar. Kavita writes about culture\, race\, gender\, and their 
 intersections. Nominated for a Pushcart Prize\, her work has been publishe
 d in WIRED\, CNN\, Teen Vogue\, Catapult\, Fast Company\, Tin House\, Long
 reads\, The Atlantic\, The Washington Post\, Los Angeles Review of Books\,
  Kenyon Review\, NBC News Asian America\, Guernica\, Electric Literature\,
  Colorlines\, The Rumpus\, and elsewhere. Kavita’s second book Craft and
  Conscience: How to Write About Social Issues (Beacon Press\, October 2022
 ) is inspired by the Writing About Social Issues class she created and tea
 ches. Her first book\, Poignant Song: The Life and Music of Lakshmi Shanka
 r\, was published by Harper Collins India in 2019. Kavita liv
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://pen.org/event/issues-in-our-stories/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Ocean: Our Liquid Universe
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T193000
UID:da2f8119c25d4498677652dcb7343ca8@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 50-300\nDid you know that the Beatles’ “Octopus’s 
 Garden” predated the discovery of four underwater habitats where 6\,000 
 pregnant female octopuses gather in geothermal waters before giving birth?
 \nSet sail with PEN America and WORDTheatre for a one-night-only theatrica
 l event celebrating our blue planet.\nThe Ocean: Our Liquid Universe\n\, w
 hich audiences of all ages into the childlike awe and wonder the sea has i
 nspired for centuries—an exhilarating fusion of music\, stories\, poetry
 \, myth\, and scientific discovery\, brought vividly to life by an all-sta
 r cast of actors\, singers\, and musicians.\nExperience selections from li
 terature such as\nThe Odyssey\nand\nThe Old Man and The Sea\nalongside mus
 ic from Radiohead’s Thom Yorke and The Beatles.\nLearn more\nProfessiona
 l members of PEN America can avail 15% off all non-VIP tickets. If you are
  a member\, please visit the member\nbenefits page\nto access the discount
  code. Not a PEN America member?\nJoin today!
LOCATION:LA
URL:https://pen.org/event/the-ocean-our-liquid-universe/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:PEN America x Film Forum: Two Prosecutors
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T194500
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T194500
UID:dcf93310556956260b201bd3031e44f6@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 17\nSoviet Union\, 1937: A newly appointed\, idealistic 
 young prosecutor is spurred to meet a prison inmate after reading a desper
 ate appeal scrawled in blood. The prosecutor recognizes this prisoner as a
  former law school professor—and is told a mortifying account of abuse a
 nd betrayal perpetrated by the secret police. He promises to report this i
 njustice to the Attorney General in Moscow\, but doesn’t realize the bur
 eaucratically murderous trap he’s stepped into. Based upon a long-unpubl
 ished novella by Soviet gulag survivor\nGeorgy Demidov\,\nTwo Prosecutors\
 npaints a hypnotic\, chilling\, blackly comic portrait of the mechanisms o
 f Great Purge-era tyranny\, with a potent contemporary resonance.\nModerat
 ed by\nLiesl Gerntholtz\n\, Managing Director\, PEN/Barbey Freedom to Writ
 e Center\, the Q&A features filmmaker\nSergei Loznitsa\n. The run time is 
 118 minutes.\nGet tickets\nProfessional members of PEN America can avail d
 iscounted tickets. Visit the\nmember benefits page\nfor more info >>\nLies
 l Gerntholtz\nis the managing director of the PEN/Barbey Freedom to Write 
 Center at PEN America. She is a South African human rights lawyer who spen
 t the early part of her career working for the South African Human Rights 
 Commission and the Commission on Gender Equality in post-apartheid South A
 frica. She was the head of the HIV Litigation Unit of the AIDS Law Project
  and the Director of the Tshwaranang Legal Advocacy Centre. In those capac
 ities\, she led high impact\, strategic litigation to advance the human ri
 ghts of people living with HIV and women affected by violence. She has liv
 ed in the US since 2008\, but remains committed to her South African roots
 \, serving on the boards of several South African human rights organisatio
 ns.\nSergei Loznitsa\nwas born on September 5th\, 1964. He grew up in Kiev
  (Ukraine)\, and in 1987\, graduated from the Kiev Polytechnic with a degr
 ee in Applied Mathematics. From 1987 to 1991\, he worked as a scientist at
  the Kiev Institute of Cybernetics\, specializing in artificial i
LOCATION:New York
URL:https://pen.org/event/two-prosecutors/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dr. Ibram X. Kendi &amp\; Friends: Chain of Ideas\, a Global Conve
 rsation
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T143000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T143000
UID:b6d666493e97de6681d6d09c0116ae9c@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:To honor the International Day for the Elimination of Racial D
 iscrimination\, please join PEN America for a free virtual conversation wi
 th the National Book Award-winning historian of\nStamped from the Beginnin
 g\n\, Dr. Ibram X. Kendi\, and leaders from human rights organizations fro
 m across the globe. Dr. Kendi’s newest book\,\nChain of Ideas: The Origi
 ns of Our Authoritarian Age\n\, charts how “great replacement theory” 
 (GRT) has moved from the margins to become the most dominant political the
 ory of our time—and what we can do to safeguard democracy from this insi
 dious threat.\nIn our fast-shifting political landscape\, most people are 
 unfamiliar with this theory’s origins and its spread\, which isn’t a c
 oincidence. In\nChain of Ideas\n\, Ibram X. Kendi uses exacting and clear 
 prose to uncover the roots of great replacement theory and its various mut
 ations around the world. It is an unsettling but indispensable global hist
 ory of how great replacement theory brought humanity into this authoritari
 an age—and how we can free ourselves from it.\nThe event will start with
  a conversation between\nDr. Kendi\nand\nRaqib Naik\n\, Executive Director
  of\nThe Center for the Study of Organized Hate\n\, examining the roots of
  GRT and the threats it presents.\nThen in conversation\nAshwini K.P.\n\, 
 the\nUN’s 6th Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of racism\n\,\nNo
 ah Bullock\,\nExecutive Director of\nCristosal\n&\nDr. Kendi\nwill discuss
  where they are seeing GRT show up today and in what forms.\nFinally\,\nDr
 . Kendi\n\,\nRethabile Ratsomo\nfrom the\nAhmed Kathrada Foundation\n\, an
 d\nZélie Heran\n\, the Head of the Legal Department at\nSOS Racisme\n\, w
 ill share the initiatives and approaches being taken to combat GRT.\nFeatu
 ring leaders from  the Center for the Study of Organized Hate\, the UN’
 s 6th Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of racism\, Cristosal\, the
  Ahmed Kathrada Foundation\, and SOS Racisme\, this event will introduce a
 ttendees to the dangers of GRT and provide a path forward.\nAbout\nChain o
 f Ideas\n:\nRecall the w
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://pen.org/event/chain-of-ideas/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Todd Purdum | Authors&#8217\; Evenings
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T170000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260323T170000
UID:3f1a7c50657d2f7d7b7de09e5507910b@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: PRIVATE\nJoin us for an intimate look at the life of\nDe
 si Arnaz: The Man Who Invented Television\nthrough the lens of expert jour
 nalist\nTodd S. Purdum.\nThis evening is generously hosted by Anya Salama.
  Books will be available for all attendees.\nAn illuminating biography of 
 Desi Arnaz\, the visionary\, trailblazing Cuban American who revolutionize
 d television and brought laughter to millions as Lucille Ball’s beloved 
 husband on\nI Love Lucy\n\, leaving a remarkable legacy that continues to 
 influence American culture today.\nDesi Arnaz is a name that resonates wit
 h fans of classic television\, but few understand the depth of his contrib
 utions to the entertainment industry. In\nDesi Arnaz\n\, Todd S. Purdum of
 fers a captivating biography that dives into the groundbreaking Latino art
 ist and businessman known to millions as Ricky Ricardo from\nI Love Lucy\n
 . Beyond his iconic role\, Arnaz was a pioneering entrepreneur who fundame
 ntally transformed the television landscape.\nHis journey from Cuban arist
 ocracy to world-class entertainer is remarkable. After losing everything d
 uring the 1933 Cuban revolution\, Arnaz reinvented himself in pre-World Wa
 r II Miami\, tapping into the rising demand for Latin music. By twenty\, h
 e had formed his own band and sparked the conga dance craze in America. Be
 hind the scenes\, he revolutionized television production by filming\nI Lo
 ve Lucy\nbefore a live studio audience with synchronized cameras\, a model
  that remains a sitcom gold standard today.\nDespite being underestimated 
 due to his accent and origins\, Arnaz’s legacy is monumental. Purdum’s
  biography\, enriched with unpublished materials and interviews\, reveals 
 the man behind the legend and highlights his enduring contributions to pop
  culture and television. This book is a must-read biography about innovati
 on\, resilience and the relentless drive of a man who changed TV forever.\
 nAbout Todd S. Purdum\nTodd S. Purdum\nis a veteran journalist and author.
  In a career of more than forty years\, he has written widely about po
LOCATION:Fisher Island
URL:https://pen.org/event/todd-purdum-authors-evenings/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jason Stanley on Erasing History with Nikole Hannah-Jones
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T190000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T190000
UID:5818a6957c038ee9056569add7e6e06c@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 16 ($38 with book purchase)\nPlease join\nJason Stanley\
 n\, author of\nErasing History: How Fascists Rewrite the Past to Control t
 he Future\n\, in conversation with\nNikole Hannah-Jones\n\, Pulitzer Prize
 -winning creator of\nThe 1619 Project\n. This ticketed event is presented 
 in collaboration with Liz’s Book Bar and One Signal Publishers\, to mark
  the arrival of\nErasing History\nin paperback.\nIn\nErasing History\n\, p
 hilosopher and New York Times bestselling author Jason Stanley exposes the
  true danger of the authoritarian right’s attacks on education\, identif
 ies their key tactics and funders\, and traces their intellectual roots. H
 e illustrates how fears of a fascist future have metastasized\, from hypot
 hetical threat to present reality. And with his “urgent\, piercing\, and
  altogether brilliant” (Johnathan M. Metzl\, author of\nWhat We’ve Bec
 ome\n) insight\, he illustrates that hearts and minds are won in our schoo
 ls and universities—places that democratic societies across the world ar
 e now ill-prepared to defend against the fascist assault currently underwa
 y.\nThis urgent discussion comes at a moment where the very acts of erasur
 e Stanley documents are occurring in the United States. From executive ord
 ers calling for an education system devoted to a mythic vision of America
 ’s past to January 6th insurrectionists rebranded as “peaceful patriot
 ic protesters.” Black history is under existential threat. Governmental 
 websites are being scrubbed of historical facts and scientific data. This 
 urgent conversation could only be had with Nikole Hannah-Jones whose 1619 
 Project saw politicians in 2020 threatening to defund schools that used cu
 rricula from it.\nJason Stanley is the Bissell-Heyd-Associates Chair in Am
 erican Studies in the Munk School of Global Affairs & Public Policy at the
  University of Toronto. He is the author of seven books\, including How Fa
 scism Works and How Propaganda Works. His writing on authoritarianism and 
 democracy has appeared in The Guardian\, the New York Times\, Project Synd
 icate\, and many other publ
LOCATION:New York
URL:https://pen.org/event/jason-stanley-erasing-history/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dr. Ibram X Kendi and William Johnson: Chain of Ideas
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T173000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T173000
UID:3d3b04a1eddcbc783d2dc2b1326b670f@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 35\nJoin The Lynx and Greater Bethel AME Church for an e
 vening with renowned author\nDr. Ibram X Kendi\n. Dr. Kendi will be in con
 versation with William Johnson\, the director of PEN America Florida\, abo
 ut his book\nChain of Ideas: The Origins of Our Authoritarian Age\n.\nRegi
 ster here\nAbout\nChain of Ideas\n:\nRecall the words chanted in Charlotte
 sville\, Virginia: “You will not replace us!” Recall the string of mas
 s shooters across the globe—in Oslo\, Christchurch\, Buffalo\, El Paso\,
  and Pittsburgh—who claimed their crimes were a defense against “White
  genocide.” Recall business and media figures cultivating anxiety and fu
 ror over demographic change.\nThese incidents only scratch the surface: Po
 pular and ruling politicians in every region of the world have expressed s
 ome version of great replacement theory\, eroding democratic norms in the 
 name of preventing demographic change. The term was coined in 2011 by a Fr
 ench novelist who argued that Black and Brown immigrants were “invading
 ” Europe\, brought by shadowy elites to “replace” the White populati
 on. From there\, politicians and theorists in the United States and elsewh
 ere repackaged it as a story of “globalists” welcoming “migrant crim
 inals” and promoting diversity to take away the jobs\, cultures\, electo
 ral power\, and very lives of White people. Over time\, great replacement 
 theory has expanded those under threat to include citizens\, men\, Jews\, 
 Christians\, heterosexuals\, and ethnic majorities in countries as distinc
 t as Russia\, El Salvador\, Brazil\, Italy\, and India\, all targeted with
  the message that they are facing an existential attack that only a strong
 man can prevent.\nIn Chain of Ideas\, internationally bestselling author D
 r. Ibram X. Kendi offers an unsettling but indispensable global history of
  how great replacement theory brought humanity into this authoritarian age
 —and how we can free ourselves from it.\nSpeakers\nDr. Ibram X. Kendi\ni
 s one of the world’s foremost historians and leading antiracist scholars
 . His books have been
LOCATION:Gainesville
URL:https://pen.org/event/dr-ibram-x-kendi-william-johnson-chain-of-ideas/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:An Evening with Christian John Wikane in Conversation with William
  Johnson
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T190000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T190000
UID:d63b106a549353ae3f19dea29b4681a0@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with\nChristian John Wikane\nas we take
  a stroll through memory lane under the disco lights.\nA Night at the Disc
 o\nis a visual time capsule of 1970s nightlife told through a photo collec
 tion featuring over 100 artists. With exclusive comments and insights from
  some of the biggest names in disco\, pop\, funk\, and punk\,\nA Night at 
 the Disco\nopens the doors to gritty underground clubs and global discotec
 hques for all music lovers to revel in.\nAn RSVP grants general entry\, bu
 t seating is not guaranteed. It is recommended that attendees arrive early
 .\nRegister here\nChristian John Wikane\nis a NYC-based music journalist a
 nd essayist. Since 2003\, he’s interviewed more than 600 recording artis
 ts\, songwriters\, and producers\, including Paul McCartney\, Janelle Mon
 áe\, Donna Summer\, Pete Seeger\, Annie Lennox\, Maurice White\, Jimmy Sc
 ott\, Carly Simon\, and Kenny Gamble. He and filmmaker Sekou Luke currentl
 y produce the video series “Unscripted: Conversations with Christian Joh
 n Wikane\,” which features his interviews with GRAMMY\, Tony\, and Emmy-
 winning artists\, and have also produced “Unscripted Live” at the Apol
 lo Theater\, City Winery\, and Lincoln Center (2024 “American Songbook
 ” series). Christian’s also a contributing writer for PEOPLE Magazine 
 and was Contributing Editor for PopMatters online magazine from 2006-2023.
 \nWilliam Johnson\nis the Director of PEN America’s Florida office. A lo
 ngtime steward in the writing community\, Johnson was the editor and publi
 sher of Mary Literary\, a literary magazine committed to showcasing work o
 f artistic integrity. He also co-produced Nepantla: A Journal Dedicated to
  Queer Poets of Color\, the first major anthology for queer poets of color
  in the United States. In 2011\, Johnson began his tenure at Lambda Litera
 ry\, an organization dedicated to promoting LGBTQ literature. As the deput
 y director of Lambda Literary\, Johnson oversaw many of the organization
 ’s most dynamic programs and public events\, including the Writer’s Re
 treat for 
LOCATION:Miami
URL:https://pen.org/event/christian-john-wikane/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
