BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ira Madison III | Authors&#8217\; Evenings
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260430T190000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260430T190000
UID:407727bca8389c851452ffbf89cd1770@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 175\nJoin us for an intimate dinner with\nIra Madison II
 I\nin celebration of his national bestseller\nPure Innocent Fun.\nThis eve
 ning is generously hosted by Linzee Troubh. Books will be available for al
 l attendees.\nIn this nostalgic and raucous collection of sixteen original
  essays\, Ira Madison III—critic\, television writer\, and host of the b
 eloved\nKeep It\npodcast—combines memoir and criticism to offer a brand-
 new pop-culture manifesto.\n“This is the most fun I’ve had reading all
  year. Like Chuck Klosterman before him\, Ira Madison III takes seriously 
 and analyzes the pop culture detritus that took up hours of our lives.”
 —Lin-Manuel Miranda\nYou can recall the first TV show\, movie\, book\, o
 r song that made you feel understood—that shaped how you live\, what you
  love\, and whom you would become. It gave you an entire worldview. For Ir
 a Madison\, that book was Chuck Klosterman’s\nSex\, Drugs\, and Cocoa Pu
 ffs\,\nwhich cemented the idea that pop culture could be a rigorous subjec
 t—and that\, for better or worse\, it shapes all of us.\nIn\nPure Innoce
 nt Fun\n\, Madison explores the key cultural moments that inspired his car
 eer as a critic and guided his coming of age as a Black gay man in Milwauk
 ee. In this hilarious\, full-throttle trip through the ’90s and 2000s\, 
 he recounts learning about sex from\nBuffy the Vampire Slayer\;\nfacing th
 e most heartbreaking election of his youth (not George W. Bush’s win\, b
 ut Jennifer Hudson losing American Idol)\; and how never getting his drive
 r’s license in high school made him just like Cher Horowitz in\nClueless
 \n: “a virgin who can’t drive.”\nBrimming with a profound love for a
  bygone culture and alternating between irreverence and heartfelt insight\
 ,\nPure Innocent Fun\n\, like all the best products of pop culture\, will 
 leave you entertained and surprisingly enlightened.\nAbout\nIra Madison II
 I\nIra Madison III\nis the host of Crooked Media’s pop culture podcast\n
 Keep It\n. His television credits include\nUncoupled\, Q-Force\n\,\nNikki 
 Fre$h\n\, and\nSo Help Me Todd\n. He has wri
LOCATION:New York
URL:https://pen.org/event/authors-evening-ira-madison-iii/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Xochitl Gonzalez | Authors&#8217\; Evenings
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260505T190000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260505T190000
UID:93e822898b6471784ced2ca3eca45c4b@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 175\nJoin us for an intimate evening of cocktails and co
 nversation with\nXochitl Gonzalez\nin celebration of her upcoming release\
 nLast Night in Brooklyn.\nThis evening is generously hosted by Sydney Rose
 . Books will be available for all attendees.\nNAMED A MOST ANTICIPATED BOO
 K OF 2026 BY TIME\, OPRAH DAILY\, USA TODAY\, PEOPLE\, HARPER’S BAZAAR\,
  LITHUB\, BOOK RIOT\, PUBLISHER’S WEEKLY\, WASHINGTON SQUARE NEWS\, AND 
 MORE!\nNew York Times bestselling author Xochitl Gonzalez delivers a capti
 vating story about a young woman whose life becomes ensnared in her glamor
 ous neighbor’s secret past\n(SPRING\, 2007) At twenty-six\, Alicia Canal
 es Forten feels smothered by her future. She’s in a long-distance relati
 onship\, living at home with her mother’s beliefs\, saving up for her we
 dding to a future doctor. But after Alicia ventures out one night in the n
 eighborhood of Fort Greene\, Brooklyn\, she finds herself lured by the sir
 en song of youth and possibility that the striving crowd of creatives hold
 s\, and moves in.\nNo one embodies this milieu more than La Garza\, a larg
 er-than-life\, up-and-coming fashion designer whose epic house parties fue
 l neighborhood lore. La Garza’s life\, observed by Alicia from her apart
 ment across the street\, seems to hold the allure and fearlessness Alicia 
 has never dared to imagine for herself.\nBut when Alicia’s wealthy banke
 r cousin moves to the neighborhood\, she finds herself increasingly drawn 
 into both his and La Garza’s precarious lives.\nAgainst the backdrop of 
 a potentially life-changing presidential election and a looming once-in-a-
 generation fiscal crisis\,\nLast Night in Brooklyn\nexplores the dark comp
 romise of the American Dream for people of color living\, unknowingly\, in
  the twilight of a cultural moment. It is a story about everything money c
 an buy—and the destruction of what it can’t.\nAbout\nXochitl Gonzalez\
 nXochitl Gonzalez\nis the New York Times bestselling author of the award-w
 inning novel\nOlga Dies\nDreaming\, the Reese’s Book Club Pick\nAnita de
  Monte Laughs Las
LOCATION:New York
URL:https://pen.org/event/xochitl-gonzalez-authors-evenings/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
